snippet.textDisplay: This is so odd...yesterday I read an article in a psychology magazine about how life seems to move faster the older you get, and how at age 40, considering you live until 80, you lived 75% of your life. The reason for this is you experience a lot of new things when you are young, everything is new, and in time life gets filled with routines, and you measure your past life in memories. Memories of new experiences will always remain so the first years of our lives seem to have lasted forever. To stop life moving so fast we need to try something new more often, which gets more difficult as you age, we cannot live a successful life by often changing partners, friends, jobs, etc., but changing things like taking a different route to work or having lunch at a different sandwich shop can make a small difference. Great subject and video Casey!

Now, more than 4 years later, I relocated to The Netherlands, my 4 years NYC chapter being a crazy adventure.
